cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper is about a neural ranking model for social media search, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (ConvNets) also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.SI (signal processing) or cs.LG (machine learning). Finally, the use of Twitter data suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.MM (multimedia).
